						<summary>

						<p>Boulder in a field about 2 kilometres to the south of the village.</p>						

						<p>MAṬLI CHIEFS.</p>						

						<p>KUMĀRA ANANTHARĀJADĒVA CHŌḌA.</p>						

						<p>1587 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka 1509, Sarvajit, Pushya, ba. 30, corresponding to January 17, Wednesday, 1587 A.D. (current).</p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. Seems to register the gift of land of one <hi rend="italic">paṁdumu</hi> by Maṭli Kumāra Anantharājadēvachōḍa Mahārāju probably to the son (name not mentioned) of certain Māchi Ayya who was maintaining this gift.</p>						

						</summary>
